phase_11() {
    run_phase 11 "Comprehensive Test Suite" "sonnet" 22 "
Read CLAUDE.md and examine EVERY file in client/src/ and server/.

Build a COMPREHENSIVE test suite. At least 150 test cases. Every test must assert real behavior — no placeholder 'renders without crashing' tests.

SETUP:
- Server: npm install --save-dev vitest supertest @vitest/coverage-v8
- Client: npm install --save-dev vitest @testing-library/react @testing-library/jest-dom @testing-library/user-event jsdom @vitest/coverage-v8
- Configure vitest in both (vitest.config.js). Add scripts: 'test', 'test:watch', 'test:coverage'. Add root 'npm test' running both.

BACKEND TESTS (server/__tests__/):

1. markdown-store.test.js (15+ tests):
   - Parse vocabulary table → correct JSON with all 8 fields
   - Parse phrases table → correct JSON with all 5 fields
   - Empty table (headers only) → empty array
   - Missing file → creates with correct headers, returns empty array
   - Malformed table (missing columns, extra pipes) → recovers, skips bad rows
   - Special chars: pipes, umlauts (ä ö ü ß), <br> tags, HTML, backticks all survive
   - Round-trip: read → write → read = identical data
   - Add entry → appears at end of file
   - Update by index → change persists, other rows untouched
   - Delete by index → removed, other rows shift correctly
   - Out-of-bounds index → throws descriptive error
   - <br> separators in case examples survive round-trip
   - Very long cell content (500+ chars) handled
   - Empty string fields stored and retrieved correctly
   - Pipe character in cell content escaped correctly

2. claude-service.test.js (mock SDK, 8+ tests):
   - Successful call → parsed JSON returned
   - Malformed JSON with markdown backticks → strips and parses
   - Malformed JSON → retries correct number of times
   - Max retries exceeded → returns structured error
   - Missing API key → clear error message
   - 429 rate limit → retries with backoff
   - Network error → user-friendly message
   - Timeout → 'timed out' error

3. anki-export.test.js (8+ tests):
   - Vocabulary entries → correct TSV with tab separation
   - Phrase entries → correct TSV
   - HTML <br> preserved in output
   - German umlauts survive encoding
   - Empty input → empty TSV (just headers or empty string)
   - Special chars (tabs, newlines in data) escaped
   - Tag format: B1::vocabulary, B2::phrases
   - Mixed vocabulary + phrases → combined TSV

4. vocabulary.test.js (supertest, 12+ tests):
   - GET /api/vocabulary → returns array
   - GET ?search=word → filters correctly
   - GET ?level=B1 → filters by level
   - GET ?since=2026-01-01 → filters by date
   - POST valid body → 201, entry added
   - POST missing required fields → 400 naming the field
   - POST empty body → 400
   - PUT /api/vocabulary/0 valid → updates
   - PUT out of bounds → 404
   - DELETE valid → removes
   - DELETE out of bounds → 404
   - Verify changes persist to markdown file after POST/PUT/DELETE

5. phrases.test.js — mirror vocabulary tests (10+ tests)

6. analyze.test.js (mock Claude, 8+ tests):
